"préférable de caster le paramètre ``authorization`` et d'accéder au mot de "
"passe directement."

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/basepath.rst:2
msgid "Basepath"
msgstr "Chemin de base"

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/basepath.rst:4
msgid ""
"The ``basepath`` middleware allow a better isolation when composing routers "
"by stripping a prefix on the :doc:`../vsgi/request` URI."
msgstr ""
"Le middleware ``basepath`` permet une meilleure isolation lors de la "
"compositions de routers en extrayant un préfix de l'URI de la :doc:`../vsgi/"
"request`."

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/basepath.rst:7
msgid ""
"The middleware strips and forwards requests which match the provided base "
"path. If the resulting path is empty, it fallbacks to a root ``/``."
msgstr ""
"Le middleware extrait un préfix du chemin et passe le résultat à la fonction "
"de rappel. Si le chemin résultant est vide, ``/`` sera utilisé."

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/basepath.rst:10
msgid ""
"Error which use their message as a ``Location`` header are automatically "
"prefixed by the base path."
msgstr ""
"Les erreurs qui utilise leurs messages pour l'en-tête ``Location`` seront "
"automatiquement préfixées."

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/basepath.rst:31
msgid ""
"If ``next`` is called while forwarding or an error is thrown, the original "
"path is restored."
msgstr ""
"Si ``next`` est applée ou une erreur est lancée depuis la fonction de "
"rappel, le chemin original sera restauré."

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/basepath.rst:46
msgid ""
"One common pattern is to provide a path-based fallback when using the :doc:"
"`subdomain` middleware."
msgstr ""
"Une approche commune est de fournir une alternative basé sur un préfix de "
"chemin avec le middleware :doc:`subdomain`."

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/basic.rst:2
msgid "Basic"
msgstr "Base"

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/basic.rst:6
msgid ""
"Previously know under the name of *default handling*, the ``basic`` "
"middleware provide a conforming handling of raised status codes as described "
"in the :doc:`../redirection-and-error` document."
msgstr ""
"Connu précédement sous le nom de gestion par défaut, le middleware ``basic`` "
"fournit une gestion conforme des codes de status décrits dans le document :"
"doc:`../redirection-and-error`."

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/basic.rst:10
msgid "It aims at providing sane defaults for a top-level middleware."
msgstr ""
"Il fournit un ensemble de comportements désirable pour un middleware situé "
"au début de la séquence."

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/basic.rst:20
msgid "If an error is caught, it will perform the following tasks:"
msgstr "Si une erreur est capturée, il s'occupe des choses suivantes:"

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/basic.rst:22
msgid "assign an appropriate status code (500 for other errors)"
msgstr "assigner un code de status approprié (500 sinon)"

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/basic.rst:23
msgid "setup required headers (eg. `Location` for a redirection)"
msgstr "il ajoute les en-têtes requises (e.g. `Location` pour une redirection)"

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/basic.rst:24
msgid ""
"produce a payload based on the message if required and not already used for "
"a header"
msgstr "produit un corps basé sur le message si requis"

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/basic.rst:27
msgid ""
"The payload will have the ``text/plain`` content type encoded with ``UTF-8``."
msgstr ""
"Le corps possède le type de contenu ``text/plain`` encodé en ``UTF-8``."

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/basic.rst:29
msgid ""
"For privacy and security reason, non-status errors (eg. ``IOError``) will "
"not be used for the payload. To enable that for specific errors, it's "
"possible to convert them into into a raised status, preferably a ``500 "
"Internal Server Error``."
msgstr ""
"Pour des raisons de sécurité, les messages d'erreur qui ne constituent pas "
"un code de status (e.g. ``IOError``) ne seront pas utilisés comme corps. "
"Pour l'utiliser de toute manière, il est possible de convertir l'erreur, "
"préférablement en ``500 Internal Server Error``."

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/content-negotiation.rst:2
msgid "Content Negotiation"
msgstr "Négotiation de contenu"

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/content-negotiation.rst:4
msgid ""
"Negotiating the resource representation is an essential part of the HTTP "
"protocol."
msgstr "Négotier une ressource est un aspect essentiel du protocole HTTP."

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/content-negotiation.rst:7
msgid ""
"The negotiation process is simple: expectations are provided for a specific "
"header, if they are met, the processing is forwarded with the highest "
"quality value, otherwise a ``406 Not Acceptable`` status is raised."
msgstr ""
"Le processus de négotiation est simple: on fournit des valeurs possibles à "
"l'aide d'une en-tête spécifique. Si elle sont satisfaites, la fonction de "
"rappel est appelé avec la valeur dont a qualité est la plus grande, "
"autrement une erreur ``406 Not Acceptable`` est lancée."

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/content-negotiation.rst:20
msgid "Or directly by using the default forward callback:"
msgstr "En utilisant directement la fonction de rappel ``forward``:"

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/content-negotiation.rst:29
msgid "Preference and quality"
msgstr "Préférence et qualité"

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/content-negotiation.rst:31
msgid ""
"Additionally, the server can state the quality of each expectation. The "
"middleware will maximize the product of quality and user agent preference "
"with respect to the order of declaration and user agent preferences if it "
"happens to be equal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/content-negotiation.rst:36
msgid ""
"If, for instance, you would serve a XML document that is just poorly "
"converted from a JSON source, you could state it by giving it a low ``q`` "
"value. If the user agent as a strong preference the former and a low "
"preference for the latter (eg. ``Accept: text/xml; application/json; "
"q=0.1)``), it will be served the version with the highest product (eg. ``0.3 "
"* 1 > 1 * 0.3``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/content-negotiation.rst:50
msgid "Error handling"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/content-negotiation.rst:52
msgid ""
"The :doc:`status` middleware may be used to handle the possible ``406 Not "
"Acceptable`` error raised if no expectation can be satisfied."
