msgid "Deal with missing resources"
msgstr "Gérer les ressources manquantes"

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/static.rst:117
msgid ""
"If a resource is not available (eg. the file does not exist), the control "
"will be forwarded to the next route."
msgstr ""
"Si une resource n,est pas disponible (e.g. le fichier n'existe pas), la "
"fonction de rappel ``next`` sera invoquée afin de passer à la prochaine "
"route."

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/static.rst:120
msgid ""
"One can use that behaviour to implement a cascading failover with the :doc:"
"`sequence` middleware."
msgstr ""
"Il est possible d'utiliser ce comportement pour implanter des alternatives "
"en cascade à l'aide du middleware :doc:`sequence`."

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/static.rst:128
msgid ""
"To generate a ``404 Not Found``, just raise a ``ClientError.NOT_FOUND`` as "
"described in :doc:`../redirection-and-error`."
msgstr ""
"Pour produire une erreur ``404 Not Found``, il est suffisant de lancer une "
"erreur ``ClientError.NOT_FOUND`` tel que décrit dans :doc:``../redirection-"
"and-error``."

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/static.rst:142
msgid "Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/static.rst:144
msgid "Options are provided as flags from the ``ServeFlags`` enumeration."
msgstr "Les options sont fournies sous la forme d'un masque ``ServeFlags``."

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/static.rst:147
msgid "ETag"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/static.rst:149
msgid ""
"If the ``ServeFlags.ENABLE_ETAG`` is specified, a checksum of the resource "
"will be generated in the ``ETag`` header."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/static.rst:152
msgid ""
"If set and available, it will have precedence over ``ServeFlags."
"ENABLE_LAST_MODIFIED`` described below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/static.rst:156
msgid "Last-Modified"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/static.rst:158
msgid ""
"Unlike ``ETag``, this caching feature is time-based and will indicate the "
"last modification on the resource. This is only available for some GFile "
"backend and will fallback to ``ETag`` if enabled as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/static.rst:162
msgid "Specify the ``ServeFlags.ENABLE_LAST_MODIFIED`` to enable this feature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/static.rst:165
msgid "X-Sendfile"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/static.rst:167
msgid ""
"If the application run behind a HTTP server which have access to the "
"resources, it might be preferable to let it serve them directly with "
"``ServeFlags.X_SENDFILE``."
msgstr ""
"Si l'application exécute derrière un proxy HTTP inversé qui a accès aux "
"ressources, il est probablement préférable de le laisser les servir "
"directement avec ``ServeFlags.X_SENDFILE``,"

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/static.rst:174
msgid "If files are not locally available, they will be served directly."
msgstr ""
"Si les fichiers ne sont pas localement disponible, ils seront servis "
"directement."

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/static.rst:177
msgid "Public caching"
msgstr "Cache publique"

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/static.rst:179
msgid ""
"The ``ServeFlags.ENABLE_CACHE_CONTROL_PUBLIC`` let intermediate HTTP servers "
"cache the payload by attaching a ``Cache-Control: public`` header to the "
"response."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/static.rst:184
msgid "Expose missing permissions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/static.rst:186
msgid ""
"The ``ServeFlags.FORBID_ON_MISSING_RIGHTS`` will trigger a ``403 Forbidden`` "
"if rights are missing to read a file. This is not a default as it may expose "
"information about the existence of certain files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/status.rst:2
msgid "Status"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/status.rst:4
msgid ""
"Thrown status codes (see :doc:`../redirection-and-error`) can be handled "
"with the ``status`` middleware."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/status.rst:7
msgid ""
"The received :doc:`../vsgi/request` and :doc:`../vsgi/response` object are "
"in the same state they were when the status was thrown. An additional "
"parameter provide access to the actual `GLib.Error`_ object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/status.rst:20
msgid ""
"To jump to the next status handler found upstream in the routing queue, just "
"throw the error. If the error can be resolved, you might want to try "
"``next`` once more."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/status.rst:39
msgid ""
"If an error is not handled, it will eventually be caught by the default "
"status handler, which produce a minimal response."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/subdomain.rst:2
msgid "Subdomain"
msgstr "Sous-domaine"

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/subdomain.rst:4
msgid ""
"The ``subdomain`` middleware matches :doc:`../vsgi/request` which subdomain "
"is conform to expectations."
msgstr ""
"Le middleware ``subdomain`` accepte les :doc:`../vsgi/request` dont le sous-"
"domaine est conforme aux attentes."

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/subdomain.rst:9
msgid ""
"Domains are interpreted in their semantical right-to-left order and matched "
"as suffix."
msgstr ""
"Les domaines sont interprétés dans l'ordre sémaitque de droite à gauche et "
"accepté par suffixe."

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/subdomain.rst:12
msgid ""
"The pattern is specified as the first argument. It may contain asterisk "
"``*`` which specify that any supplied label satisfy that position."
msgstr ""
"Le patron est spécifié en premier argument. Il peut contenir des astérisques "
"``*`` qui spécifient que tout libellé fourni sera satisfait à cette position."

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/subdomain.rst:26
msgid "The matched subdomain labels are extracted and passed by parameter."
msgstr ""
"Les libellés correspondant du domaine de la requête sont extrait et passé à "
"la fonction de rappel."

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/subdomain.rst:34
msgid ""
"This middleware can be used along with subrouting to mount any :doc:`../"
"router` on a specific domain pattern."
msgstr ""
"Ce middleware peut être utilisé pour monter un :doc:`../router` à l'aide de "
"sous-routage sur un patron de domaine spécifique."

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/subdomain.rst:45
msgid "Strict"
msgstr "Mode strict"

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/subdomain.rst:47
msgid ""
"There is two matching mode: loose and strict. The loose mode only expect the "
"request to be performed on a suffix-compatible hostname. For instance, "
"``api`` would match ``api.example.com`` and ``v1.api.example.com`` as well."
msgstr ""
"Il existe deux mode de comparaison: flexible et stricte. Le mode flexible "
"vérifie uniquement que le domaine de la requête possède un suffixe "
"compatible. Par exemple, ``api`` accepte ``api.example.com`` et ``v1.api."
"example.com``."

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/subdomain.rst:51
msgid ""
"To prevent this and perform a _strict_ match, simply specify the second "
"argument. The domain of the request will have to supply exactly the same "
"amount of labels matching the expectations."
msgstr ""
"Afin de prevenir çela et d'effectuer une comparaison stricte, il suffit de "
"spécifier le deuxième argument. Le domaine de la requête devra comporter "
"exactement le même nombre de libellés."

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/subdomain.rst:61
msgid "Skip labels"
msgstr "Libellés ignorés"

#: ../../../docs/middlewares/subdomain.rst:63
msgid ""
"By default, the two first labels are ignored since web applications are "
"typically served under two domain levels (eg. example.com). If it's not the "
"case, the number of skipped labels can be set to any desirable value."
msgstr ""
"Par défaut, les deux premiers libellés sont ignorés puisqu'une application "
"Web est normalement desservie sous deux niveaux de domaines (e.g. example."
"com). Dans le cas contraire, il est possible de définir le nombre de "
"libellés à ignorer."
